                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.115/10–2449: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">McConaughy</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-10-24T13:00:00+08:00"
                            >October 24, 1949—1 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received October 24—2:46 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4491. A. P. Pattison, Shanghai agent Isbrandtsen Company, informs Consulate
                    General [that] SS <hi rend="italic">Flying Cloud</hi> ETD Hong Kong October 24
                    or 25 for Shanghai. Cargo for Shanghai discharged about 6,000 tons.</p>
                <p>Sent Department 4491, repeated Hong Kong 334.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">McConaughy</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
